abstract: A collection of notable articles, videos and blog posts on food, farming and policy from the food journalist and activist.
snippet: A collection of notable articles, videos and blog posts on food, farming and policy from the food journalist and activist.
lead_paragraph: In the introduction to his essay on the Obama administration’s failure to take on corporate agriculture in this week’s Food Issue, Michael Pollan writes about an open letter to the president that he published in the magazine eight years ago. Pollan has been writing for The Times much longer, starting with his articles in the magazine about lawns and gardens in the 1980s. Since then he has primarily examined all the complicated ways we obtain the food we eat.

abstract: The Golf Sportwagen Alltrack’s pressed look is less Eddie Bauer, more Banana Republic. It has off-road capabilities but is comfortable on the highway.

lead_paragraph: Adding ground clearance, all-wheel drive and rugged Ranger Rick cladding to a station wagon is a well-known path for automotive profit.

abstract: The Genesis has been Hyundai’s upmarket sedan. Now the name has become the automaker’s luxury brand, spiffing up that car and adding the flagship G90.
snippet: The Genesis has been Hyundai’s upmarket sedan. Now the name has become the automaker’s luxury brand, spiffing up that car and adding the flagship G90.
lead_paragraph: A NEW luxury brand is arriving in the United States with two sedans, one of them a repurposed model already available here.

headline_main: Video Review: With Genesis, Hyundai Brings a New Luxury Brand to Town
headline_print_headline: A Luxury Brand Is Born in a Hyundai Showroom

abstract: In small-town Iowa, conservative Christians say they feel abandoned, with no true champion in the presidential race and a country that they believe has turned its back.
snippet: In small-town Iowa, conservative Christians say they feel abandoned, with no true champion in the presidential race and a country that they believe has turned its back.
lead_paragraph: GRIMES, Iowa — Betty and Dick Odgaard used to own the tiny church next door to their home. They had built it over 13 years into an art gallery, bistro, flower shop and framing service. They even rented out the chapel, with its bright stained glass windows, for social events.

abstract: Epstein helped the Boston Red Sox end an 86-year World Series title drought. Expectations are high he can duplicate the feat with the playoff-bound Chicago Cubs.

lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Five years ago, Theo Epstein took a job that even his friends called career suicide.
